This repository starts with a minimal, self-contained governance baseline. The
same checks run locally and in `.github/workflows/devguard.yml`.

## PowerShell quick start

Run these commands from the project root:

```powershell
py -3.11 -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pip install -r requirements-dev.txt
git init
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pre_commit install --hook-type pre-commit --hook-type commit-msg
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts\devguard.py verify --require-hooks
```

The fourth command installs **both** the normal `pre-commit` gate and the
`commit-msg` gate. A successful verification prints `DEVGUARD OK`; every missing
dependency, file, configuration link, or required hook returns a non-zero exit.

## Daily commands

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pre_commit run --all-files
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest -q
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts\devguard.py verify --require-hooks
```

## Project records

- Current state: `STATUS.md`
- Work plan: `docs/plan/开发清单.md`
- Decisions and constraints: `CLAUDE.md`
- Per-change evidence: `worklogs/`

Keep documentation and implementation in the same pull request. Protect the
default branch in the hosting service and require the `governance` CI check;
local hooks alone are intentionally not presented as server-side enforcement.
